To learn more about the Plan's documentation requirements based on the Authorized Individual type, please view Plan Document Requirements.
If the Plan requires documentation confirming the Authorized Individual's relationship to the Account Owner and authority to manage the Account, you can upload the documentation through the Upload documents screen. Note that Accounts are placed in a pending status until required documentation is submitted to and approved by the Plan. Accounts are unable to receive contributions while in a pending status. Any contributions received for a pending Account will be held until the pending status is resolved.

Ugift® - Give the gift of savings
Ugift is an easy-to-use, no-cost way for ABLE Account Owners and Authorized Individuals to invite others to make contributions to the ABLE Account. The Account has a unique Ugift code to share with friends and family so they can contribute to the Account at UgiftABLE.com

Go to the Account

To apply for an account as an Authorized Individual on behalf of the Account Owner, the applicant must provide official documents confirming the applicant's relationship to the Account Owner, and the applicant's authority to open and manage the account. Documents can be uploaded during the online application process. Appropriate documents must be uploaded (or otherwise provided) and approved by the Program Manager before the account will be activated.


Typical documentation is listed below for each Authorized Individual type. In some cases, other documents might be required to establish the applicant's authority and relationship to the account owner. Please contact the Program Manager if documentation is not available or if you have questions about documentation requirements.


Applicants may provide scans or copies of any required documents with the application but should maintain originals or certified copies and be able to produce them for the Program Manager or Internal Revenue Service upon request.


Authorized Individual Type:Typical Documentation:
Power of AttorneyPower of attorney signed by the Account Owner
ConservatorLetters of appointment issued by a court
Legal GuardianLetters of appointment issued by a court, granting appropriate financial authority
SpouseMarriage certificate
ParentAccount Owner's birth certificate confirming applicant is the Account Owner's parent
SiblingNC ABLE Affidavit
GrandparentNC ABLE Affidavit
SSA-appointed Representative PayeeDocumentation issued by the Social Security Administration appointing applicant as representative payee
